According to the Guttmacher Institute, in 2009, Saint Lucia’s government amended its penal code to add the use of “any instrument” for the purpose of “getting rid” of a child. The law was instituted so that abortion would become illegal under all circumstances.

Charges of rape or incest would not guarantee pardons for abortion. To gain a permit, the request must be vetted and approved by the Minister of Health and Wellness.

In December 2018, a Bronze Alliance affiliate in Texas began court hearings after the City of El Paso attempted to ban abortions. Pro-life groups hope the El Paso case will be appealed all the way to the U.S. Supreme Court so the Court will re-evaluate their 1973 summary that created a “Right to Abort” across the United States in the Roe v. Wade decision.

Texas will be the first state to ask America’s highest Court to reconsider the Roe v. Wade decision. Regardless of the decision in the new Texas case, all states have a legal Right to Criminalize and Actual Ban Abortion. Even conservative states like Tennessee and Kentucky have recently criminalized abortion in their cities and towns, saving thousands of lives.
